retweeted_text: If Speaker Pelosi was serious about helping the US Postal Service she would bring a bipartisan bill like the Postal Service Reform Act of 2017 to the floor for a vote. Meaningful solutions have been proposed but Dem leadership has failed to make these necessary reforms a reality.

full_text: There is no question that reforms are absolutely necessary for the future of the USPS. Right now, USPS has over $10 billion cash on hand. We can wait until after this election to implement the reforms that USPS needs to remain a solvent service for the American people.

Reservists & @IowaNatGuard members deserve the same access to transitional skills training & job placement as our active duty servicemembers.

Yesterday, @RepTimmons & I hosted a roundtable to talk about our bipartisan bill, the Transition for Success Act: https://t.co/KKBwghfyKf https://t.co/fqckOJL6GJ

full_text: Welcome to the beautiful Upstate of business-friendly South Carolina! We are happy to have you. https://t.co/ArwnhLeX7L

Three years ago today brave law enforcement officers saved my life when my colleagues and I were attacked on the baseball field.

Important to remember: Every day police officers risk their lives to serve and protect communities across America.

We can‚Äôt turn our backs on them. https://t.co/WH4Q2TkiBj

full_text:
As Congress considers legislation on police reforms, it is imperative that we have better data to allow us the ability to make informed policy decisions with the aim of restoring trust between law enforcement and the people they serve in every community.

full_text: I am pleased to announce that Greenville County will be receiving a $1,935,622 federal grant as part of the bipartisan CARES Act to support homeless families and individuals affected by COVID-19. This will help ensure no person experiencing homelessness in SC is left behind.

full_text: My office received word late last week that Donaldson Field Airport in Greenville will be receiving a $2.75 million grant from the @USDOT. This grant will be used to rehabilitate the taxiway and allow Donaldson Field and @SCTAC to continue to be a leader in our state.

retweeted_text: We paid out $53 million dollars in FPUC (Federal Pandemic Unemployment Compensation) benefits yesterday to 64,000 South Carolinians. Check your portal under "payments" on your MyBenefits homepage. It will take 24-72 hours to show in your bank account.

full_text: We are praying for everyone across South Carolina who has been impacted by the severe storms. We know there are many folks in the Upstate without power. You can report outages here: https://t.co/J6iOq6EIhJ

full_text:

As always, please let me know if my office or I can be of assistance during this time. (5/5)

H.Res 756, the ‚ÄúMoving Our Democracy and Congressional Operations Towards Modernization,‚Äù also known as ‚ÄúModCom‚Äù is on the verge to be passed by the U.S. House of Representatives!

full_text:

I am proud to be a part of this committee and am thankful for the leadership of @RepDerekKilmer and @RepTomGraves.

I am heartbroken to hear of the tragic shootings in Texas and Ohio. Thank you to the first responders for their quick actions. 

This is not who we are as a country. Far too many families have been torn apart because of senseless actions like these. 

We must do better.
